Aromatherapy is a rapidly growing market that is segmented based on product type, application, and distribution channel. The product type segment includes essential oils, carrier oils, blended oils, and equipment. Essential oils are witnessing significant demand due to their various therapeutic benefits such as reducing stress, improving sleep, and boosting mood. Carrier oils are used to dilute essential oils and are popular in skincare products. Blended oils are combinations of different essential oils to create unique scents and therapeutic effects. Equipment like diffusers and nebulizers are essential for dispersing aromas effectively. In terms of applications, aromatherapy is used for relaxation, skincare, pain management, and treating colds and coughs. The distribution channels for aromatherapy products include online retail, offline retail, specialty stores, and supermarkets/hypermarkets.

