The global aromatherapy market is experiencing robust growth attributed to the increasing adoption of holistic wellness practices and rising consumer awareness regarding the therapeutic benefits of essential oils. The market is segmented based on product type, mode of delivery, application, distribution channel, and end-user. The consumables segment, including essential oils, carrier oils, and blended oils, dominates the market due to the growing demand for natural and organic products. The equipment segment, comprising diffusers and nebulizers, is witnessing steady growth as consumers seek effective ways to disperse aromas for various applications.

In terms of the mode of delivery, topical application remains a popular choice for skincare and massage therapies, while direct inhalation and aerial diffusion are favored for relaxation, stress relief, and managing respiratory issues. Applications such as pain management, scar management, and cold and cough treatments are driving the demand for aromatherapy products across various consumer segments. The distribution channels play a crucial role in reaching a

 

